  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vanuatu: Building Capacity to Address Climate Change and Disaster-Induced Displacement Phase II</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following a project to build the capacity of the Government of Vanuatu (GoV) which created the Vanuatu National Policy on Climate Change and Disaster-Induced Displacement, this follow-up project intends to providetechnical support to the GoV towards the implementation of the recommendations and strategic plans outlined in the displacement policy.The project will establish a committee dedicated to the implementation of the displacement policy and publish a policy brief on the displacement policy to guide the revision of National Disaster Act, Disaster Risk Management Bill, and Provincial Disaster Risk Management Plan. The project will also support the development of protection-centered guidelines to assist the GoV and other stakeholders in identifying appropriate durable solutions.</narrative>
  </description>
